content: Had a great birthday dinner with family. Reflecting on turning 22, I realize this year is about resetting my career path, learning from my past, and exploring new avenues in trading.
Spent the last few days brushing up on Rust. Managed to optimize a trading bot's performance by 20%. It's rewarding to see code translate into real-world impact.
Just had a coffee meeting with a potential mentor in algorithmic trading. We discussed the nuances of high-frequency trading strategies. Exciting but challenging road ahead.
Went to a blockchain meetup last night. Met someone from DeFi, talked about integrating $XVI into trading platforms. Might be a new direction worth exploring.
Back at it with Rust. Today, I tackled memory management issues in my latest project. It's like playing chess with the computer, but when you win, the payoff is huge.
Family dinner tonight. Shared my recent job loss and the path I'm considering. Their support is invaluable as I navigate this transition.
Caught up with an old friend from college. He's doing well in finance. We brainstormed potential projects that could combine quant trading with blockchain technology.
Had a breakthrough with my trading strategy. Managed to backtest a new approach that shows promise. Feels good to make progress, even if it's small.
Received some feedback on my trading bot from a senior trader. He pointed out some inefficiencies in my code. Time to refine and optimize.
Just joined a quant trading forum. Already made some connections. One member offered to share insights on market analysis techniques. This community could be a goldmine.
Pitched my idea for a new trading strategy at a local tech startup. They're intrigued but want more proof of concept. Back to the drawing board, but it's a step forward.
Family day today. Took a walk in Central Park with my parents. Their advice and perspective are helping me stay grounded during this career pivot.
Had an interview for a junior quant role. It was tough, but I felt prepared. Waiting to hear back. Meanwhile, I'm coding a new feature for my trading bot.
Celebrated a friend's birthday. Life's not just about work. Yet, even in casual conversations, ideas for trading strategies pop up. Networking never stops.
Just got an email from a potential mentor. He's willing to guide me in my trading career. This could be the breakthrough I needed. Exciting times ahead in NYC.
